"Double quote" every literal that contains spaces/metacharacters and _every_ expansion: "a & b", "$var", "${array[@]}", "$(command)". Use 'single quotes' for code or to make something literal: 'Costs $5 US', ssh host 'echo "$HOSTNAME"'. See <http://mywiki.wooledge.org/Quotes>, <http://mywiki.wooledge.org/Arguments> and <http://wiki.bash-hackers.org/syntax/words>.
